# Model bindings

Concrete role IDs exist only in `.cursor/agent-workflow-skills/model-routing.jsonc`.
Read that machine-local JSONC binding through `dispatch_resolver.py`; this rule
never renders or duplicates an ID. `reason: null` reuses `build`. Review must
remain independent; the installer enforces ID inequality, not model-family
identity.

Before every native subagent dispatch, run the installed `dispatch_resolver.py` for the selected role. If Cursor exposes its model registry, supply the full list and fail when `requested_model` is absent. Pass the returned `subagent_type` and exact `model` fields without fallback. Cursor review uses model-configurable `generalPurpose`, not built-in `explore`.

Review has a read-only contract: it inspects and reports without writing files. The native Cursor dispatch arguments used by this bundle provide no platform-enforced read-only permission, so the review capsule must state the contract and the parent keeps editing authority.

Record `role`, `requested_model`, `actual_model`, `actual_model_source`, and `cross_model`. No current SDK adapter is shipped because official SDK telemetry field support is not established. The installed resolver accepts no actual-model or source argument and always emits `actual_model=null`, `actual_model_source=null`, `cross_model=unverified`, and `review_kind=independent-review-unverified` for review; family labels cannot change that result.

A future adapter must parse a genuine SDK run/result object in a controlled runtime, not CLI input. Until then, CLI values, UI labels, self-reports, and generic library callers must not create runtime-model or cross-model claims.
